</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="24CA7856D70F6DB8ACBADBCAC252B84A" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="B4EE92F275075D003749E588DD65A1A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139">
<taxonomicName id="DC5815890EF2155C9392E5D9A8F94458" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pseudodoros" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudodoros (Pseudodoros) nigricollis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricollis" subGenus="Pseudodoros">Pseudodoros (Pseudodoros) nigricollis</taxonomicName>
The current consensus is that the genus 
<taxonomicName id="ECE14A69B59B478060829C1CF395DC2E" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pseudodoros" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudodoros" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudodoros</taxonomicName>
Becker, 1903 consists of two subgenera (
<taxonomicName id="2A4EF932532CB521364B369205E153EA" authority="Hull, 1949" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Dioprosopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dioprosopa" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dioprosopa</taxonomicName>
Hull, 1947 (
<bibRefCitation id="47AF4F8AD3005AE55F8182DEDC30E620" author="Hull, FM" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Americana" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" pagination="89 - 291" title="The genus Baccha from the New World" volume="27" year="1947">Hull 1947</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="1A98F62077AEED0F4BB96E60FD08686D" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pseudodoros" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudodoros" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudodoros</taxonomicName>
with three described species: 
<taxonomicName id="49170A1D1E0B4ED9FA4DE1EDB89122F1" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. (Dioprosopa) clavata" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavata" subGenus="Dioprosopa">P. (Dioprosopa) clavata</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius, 1794), 
<taxonomicName id="1800DA33A2684297674B3E87BF9AB03F" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. (Dioprosopa) vockerothi" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vockerothi" subGenus="Dioprosopa">P. (Dioprosopa) vockerothi</taxonomicName>
(Kassebeer, 2000) and 
<taxonomicName id="6C60B1EBA02210CB860844A60B0F169E" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. (Pseudodoros) nigricollis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricollis" subGenus="Pseudodoros">P. (Pseudodoros) nigricollis</taxonomicName>
Becker, 1903. A review of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="E306A17E8B013C59DA369C74BF2FD6F9" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pseudodoros" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudodoros" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudodoros</taxonomicName>
was undertaken by Kassebeer (2000) in which he described a new species from South America and concluded that the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="F29277F8BFE067DDA720CC6D1A0E91B8" authority="Hull, 1949" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Dioprosopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dioprosopa" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dioprosopa</taxonomicName>
should have generic status with the genus 
<taxonomicName id="DD48B1F5D2A93A62BBF87D12227C3520" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pseudodoros" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudodoros" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudodoros</taxonomicName>
restricted to the Eastern Mediterranean and Afrotropics and 
<taxonomicName id="916133C2B90CBCFCCADFC4F82A95CAC2" authority="Hull, 1949" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Dioprosopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dioprosopa" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dioprosopa</taxonomicName>
to the New World. A fourth species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C46C26021DDE3884B21F1CF8500910A" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. psyllidivora" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psyllidivora">P. psyllidivora</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="35CE9777451824A341F9C3F29788B2B6" originalValue="SÃ©guy">Seguy</normalizedToken>
, 1953 was synomymised by 
<bibRefCitation id="B82A0F962590E942E7FD3A642874B4B6" author="Kassebeer, C" journalOrPublisher="Dipteron" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" pagination="73 - 92" title="Zur Gattung Pseudodoros Becker, 1903 (Diptera, Syrphidae)" volume="3" year="2000">Kassebeer (2000)</bibRefCitation>
with 
<taxonomicName id="BC29A51EDDBD252CA2775F7267870016" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Allobaccha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Allobaccha sapphirina" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sapphirina">Allobaccha sapphirina</taxonomicName>
(Wiedemann, 1830). 
<bibRefCitation id="7803BEDC20DE21FF9E13112C68510552" author="Mengual, X" journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" pagination="543 - 562" title="First phylogeny of predatory Flower flies (Diptera, Syrphidae, Syrphinae) using mitochondrial COI and nuclear 28 S rRNA genes: conflict andcongruence with the current tribal classification" volume="24" year="2008">Mengual et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, in their study on the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="9F657D17E504F2AD4AEF4974E2E5264B" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" rank="tribe" tribe="Syrphini">Syrphini</taxonomicName>
, recognised 
<taxonomicName id="E6B4AC9B240C21A18A1344CD0ED10D80" authority="Hull, 1949" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Dioprosopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dioprosopa" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dioprosopa</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="D9F45AFF8F4E76ABEEF1573F4F334F97" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Pseudodoros" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudodoros" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudodoros</taxonomicName>
. The holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="D4BAE5CC3F016654EBF89EB126E03CEF" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. nigricollis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricollis">P. nigricollis</taxonomicName>
is a male specimen from Cairo, Egypt, collected by Becker in November 1898. Becker published the description of the genus and species in 1903 (
<bibRefCitation id="54042669320675D8453339629C9A0C2B" author="Becker, Th" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" pagination="67 - 195" title="Aegyptische Dipteren" volume="II. Band Heft 3" year="1903">Becker 1903</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="210C3B53E4DA2444AB528DE52C0082E7" author="Becker, Th" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" pagination="1 - 66" title="Aegyptische Dipteren" volume="II. Band Heft 2" year="1902">Becker 1902</bibRefCitation>
). Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="7A186B1E84187736FCC150F0A9E24928" author="Efflatoun, H" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe Entomologique d'Egypte. Cairo." pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" pagination="1 - 160" title="A monograph of Egyptian Diptera (Part I. Fam. Syrphidae)" volume="2" year="1922">Efflatoun (1922)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned two males from Ghezireh (which nowadays is part of Cairo), one recorded from spring 1909 and the other without date. Efflatoun's redescription (mostly a direct translation) was based primarily on Becker's description, with additional characters from his two specimens. In his review, 
<bibRefCitation id="202C7FE1432348546DE70F2242D57A2B" author="Kassebeer, C" journalOrPublisher="Dipteron" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" pagination="73 - 92" title="Zur Gattung Pseudodoros Becker, 1903 (Diptera, Syrphidae)" volume="3" year="2000">Kassebeer (2000)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the male of 
<taxonomicName id="A5773BDD0A07FDE4D81EE482394EFBA3" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. nigricollis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricollis">P. nigricollis</taxonomicName>
using the holotype, added further morphological characteristics of the female to those provided for both sexes by 
<bibRefCitation id="90BB947BD1743ABB12216B1217F4BE13" author="Sack, P." editor="Lindner, E." journalOrPublisher="Die Fliegen der Palaerktischen Region Band" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" volume="IV" year="1932">Sack (1932)</bibRefCitation>
and figured both male and female abdomens. He also agreed with 
<bibRefCitation id="AFBC9488B85E49739A3A747DAB8D446F" author="Smith, K" editor="Crosskey, R. W." journalOrPublisher="London" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" title="Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afrotropical Region" year="1980">Smith and Vockeroth (1980)</bibRefCitation>
that 
<taxonomicName id="D9A5042BF964085338232B9D760EB355" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Baccha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Baccha extranea" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="extranea">Baccha extranea</taxonomicName>
Bezzi 1915 is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="0058278E8B74CCE2E951059BCFB84743" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. nigricollis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricollis">P. nigricollis</taxonomicName>
. However, he made no reference to Efflatoun's paper or specimens. According to Efflatoun (1922), a male from 1909 was in his private collection (in Cairo) and the other one in the collection of what was called the Sultania Agricultural Society, also based in Cairo. Where these specimens are at present is unknown to the authors. Also it is unknown which females were used by 
<bibRefCitation id="5D233D2797EF68770AAF82C8B4738494" author="Sack, P." editor="Lindner, E." journalOrPublisher="Die Fliegen der Palaerktischen Region Band" pageId="0" pageNumber="8139" volume="IV" year="1932">Sack (1932)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
